{"parse":{"title":"Religious fraud","pageid":10482222,"revid":845312927,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Religious fraud</b> is a term used for <a href=\"/wiki/Civil_law_(common_law)\" title=\"Civil law (common law)\">civil</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> or <a href=\"/wiki/Criminal_law\" title=\"Criminal law\">criminal</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Fraud\" title=\"Fraud\">fraud</a> carried out in the name of a religion<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> or within a religion, e.g. false claims to being <a href=\"/wiki/Kosher\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Kosher\">kosher</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> or <a href=\"/wiki/Tax_fraud\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Tax fraud\">tax fraud</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>A specific form of religious fraud is <b><a href=\"/wiki/Pious_fraud\" title=\"Pious fraud\">pious fraud</a></b> (Latin: <i>pia fraus</i>), whereby one employs lies and/or deception in order to convince others of the truth of one's own religion or specific religious claims. Sometimes these involve '<a href=\"/wiki/White_lie\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"White lie\">white lies</a>': the perpetrator may think it more important to make others accept a certain belief than that the method is truthful; this <a href=\"/wiki/Consequentialism\" title=\"Consequentialism\">end justifies the means</a> of a lie.<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> A well-known example is the <a href=\"/wiki/Shroud_of_Turin\" title=\"Shroud of Turin\">Shroud of Turin</a>, a <a href=\"/wiki/Late_Medieval\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Late Medieval\">late Medieval</a> fabrication that supposedly was the clothing in which <a href=\"/wiki/Historical_Jesus\" title=\"Historical Jesus\">Jesus</a> would have been buried in the 1st century.<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Religious_fraud&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Civil Law: Using Secular Law to Assure Observance of Practices with Religious \u2026\nK Greenawalt - South California Law Review, 1997</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">On Balance: Religious Liberty and Third-Party Harms. JC Lipson - Minnesota Law Review, 1999</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Privilege, Posture and Protection Religion in the Law; Weiss, Jonathan. Yale Law Journal. 593 (1963-1964)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Profit without honor: White-collar crime and the looting of America. SM Rosoff, HN Pontell, RH Tillman</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Kosher Fraud Statutes and the Establishment Clause: Are They Kosher? MA Berman - Colum. JL &amp; Soc. Probs., 1992</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">University of Dayton Law Review (1997-1998).  Can Kosher Fraud Statutes Pass the Lemon Test: The Constitutionality of Current and Proposed Statutes; Lindsay, Karen Ruth Lavy</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">The effect of religiosity on tax fraud acceptability: A cross-national analysis. S Stack, A Kposowa, 2006</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Weiland, P. (1858). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.dbnl.org/tekst/weil004kuns01_01/weil004kuns01_01_0016.php#p1166\"><i>Kunstwoordenboek, of verklaring van allerhande vreemde woorden, benamingen, gezegden en spreekwijzen, die, uit verscheidene talen ontleend, in de zamenleving en in geschriften, betreffende alle vakken van kunsten, wetenschappen en geleerdheid, voorkomen</i></a> (in Dutch). Rotterdam: D. Bolle<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">10 June</span> 2018</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Kunstwoordenboek%2C+of+verklaring+van+allerhande+vreemde+woorden%2C+benamingen%2C+gezegden+en+spreekwijzen%2C+die%2C+uit+verscheidene+talen+ontleend%2C+in+de+zamenleving+en+in+geschriften%2C+betreffende+alle+vakken+van+kunsten%2C+wetenschappen+en+geleerdheid%2C+voorkomen.&amp;rft.place=Rotterdam&amp;rft.pub=D.+Bolle&amp;rft.date=1858&amp;rft.aulast=Weiland&amp;rft.aufirst=P.&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.dbnl.org%2Ftekst%2Fweil004kuns01_01%2Fweil004kuns01_01_0016.php%23p1166&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AReligious+fraud\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-9\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Robert Tod Carroll (24 January 2014). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://skepdic.com/piousfraud.html\">\"pious fraud\"</a>. <i>The Skeptic's Dictionary</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">10 June</span> 2018</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Skeptic%27s+Dictionary&amp;rft.atitle=pious+fraud&amp;rft.date=2014-01-24&amp;rft.au=Robert+Tod+Carroll&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fskepdic.com%2Fpiousfraud.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AReligious+fraud\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:P_religion_world.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/28/P_religion_world.svg/35px-P_religion_world.svg.png\" width=\"35\" height=\"32\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/28/P_religion_world.svg/53px-P_religion_world.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/28/P_religion_world.svg/70px-P_religion_world.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"400\" data-file-height=\"360\" /></a></td><td><i>This <a href=\"/wiki/Religion\" title=\"Religion\">religion</a>-related article is a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Stub\" title=\"Wikipedia:Stub\">stub</a>. You can help Wikipedia by <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Religious_fraud&amp;action=edit\">expanding it</a>.</i><div 